    "id": "8751",
    "title": "Nausea and vomiting in pregnancy",
    "slug": "nausea-and-vomiting-in-pregnancy",
    "date": "2020-07-01",
    "content": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What Is Nausea and Vomiting in Pregnancy (NVP)?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nausea and vomiting in pregnancy is a very common symptom experienced during the first trimester. It is called morning sickness, although the symptoms can happen at any time of the day. Pregnant women in their first trimester begin feeling uneasy around food, smells, or even on an empty stomach.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some women only feel mild nausea, while others may vomit several times a day. It's common for early pregnancy questions like “feeling like vomiting but not actually vomiting, am I pregnant?” to arise since hormonal changes can cause queasiness even before a pregnancy is confirmed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Typically, nausea begins around the sixth week and improves by the second trimester. However, every woman is different. For some, nausea may stop at 7 weeks while for others, it might last beyond the second trimester.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Causes Vomiting During Pregnancy?&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are several causes of vomiting during pregnancy. The biggest reason is hormonal changes, especially rising hCG and estrogen levels during early pregnancy. Other common causes include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Increased sensitivity to smell</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Slower digestion during pregnancy</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Stress and fatigue</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You might wonder if during pregnancy vomiting is good or bad. Mild nausea and vomiting are usually considered normal signs of pregnancy hormones working in the body. However excessive vomiting should not be ignored.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Severe vomiting may sometimes point towards&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.fda.gov/consumers/knowledge-and-news-women-owh-blog/beyond-morning-sickness-hyperemesis-gravidarum\">hyperemesis gravidarum symptoms</a>, a condition that can lead to dehydration and weight loss.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Treatment for Nausea and Vomiting in Pregnancy&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nausea and vomiting in pregnancy treatment depends on how severe the symptoms are. Mild symptoms can be managed with simple lifestyle and diet changes. Here are some commonly recommended tips:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Eat frequent small meals instead of a one big meal</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Avoid spicy, oily or strong smelling food</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Drink fluids slowly throughout the day</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Get proper rest and sleep</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Avoid staying hungry for long periods</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you ask a doctor how to stop nausea during pregnancy, he may prescribe vitamin supplements or anti-nausea medicines if symptoms become difficult to manage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are planning a pregnancy, consulting an experienced&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/advanced-fertility-treatments/\">fertility specialist in Kolkata</a>&nbsp;or exploring&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/fertility-support-services/\">fertility support services in Kolkata</a>&nbsp;can help you receive the right guidance, care, and support throughout your journey.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Foods and Diet Tips to Reduce Nausea and Vomiting in Pregnancy&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Diet can make a big difference in controlling nausea during pregnancy. Bland and easy to digest foods like bananas, rice, toast, dry khakhra, and moong dal khichdi are usually gentle on the stomach.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many of our patients have found relief in cold foods like smoothies, watermelon, or chilled yogurt. Sipping fluids through the day and trying natural remedies like ginger tea, ginger or mint candies may help soothe queasiness and morning sickness symptoms.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Women receiving care through&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/all-services/\">Fertility &amp; Gynecological Services in Kolkata</a>&nbsp;are often guided with personalized diet recommendations based on their symptoms.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">When Should You Consult a Doctor for Pregnancy Vomiting?&nbsp;</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You should speak to your doctor if vomiting becomes severe. If you are unable to keep liquids down for 8 to 12 hours or cannot eat solid food for an entire day, it is important to seek medical attention.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Signs like dizziness, very dark urine, dehydration, rapid weight loss, extreme weakness, fainting, or vomiting several times a day should not be ignored. You should also contact your doctor immediately if you notice blood in your vomit, develop fever or abdominal pain. Or feel too exhausted to function normally.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For proper pregnancy care and guidance, consult Dr. Rajeev Agarwal, a trusted&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/advanced-fertility-treatments/\">fertility specialist in Kolkata</a>. He is also an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://drrajeevagarwal.co.in/\">IVF specialist in Kolkata</a>&nbsp;with over 70% of success rate, helping many couples experience the joy of parenthood.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nausea and vomiting are common during pregnancy and are usually caused by hormonal changes. While mild symptoms are normal, severe vomiting requires medical attention. Understanding what is morning sickness in pregnancy and following the right care tips can help make this phase of pregnancy more comfortable.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How can you safely reduce nausea during pregnancy?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eating small meals, staying hydrated, avoiding trigger foods, and following proper nausea and vomiting in pregnancy treatment methods can help reduce symptoms safely.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">When does morning sickness start and when does it stop?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Morning sickness usually starts around the sixth week of pregnancy and often improves by the second trimester.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What is hyperemesis gravidarum and how is it treated?</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hyperemesis gravidarum is a severe form of pregnancy vomiting that may require medications, IV fluids and close medical care.&nbsp;<strong> </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<p>"
